══ Shopping-only baseline: decomposition summary ═══
                                mean     std
naive_RMSE                    1.3163  0.0021
adapted_RMSE                  1.3114  0.0003
shopping_only_RMSE            1.3115  0.0012
domain_shift_recoverable_gap  0.0048  0.0024
adaptation_captured_gap       0.0050  0.0022
adaptation_capture_ratio      1.0607  0.1703

  Reading guide:
    domain_shift_recoverable_gap = naive_RMSE - shopping_only_RMSE
      → total error attributable to being trained on the wrong
        domain at all (large positive = genuine domain shift cost).
    adaptation_captured_gap = naive_RMSE - adapted_RMSE
      → how much of that gap the paper's fine-tuning recipe
        actually recovers.
    adaptation_capture_ratio = adaptation_captured_gap / domain_shift_recoverable_gap
      → fraction of the recoverable domain-shift gap captured
        by adaptation; near 1.0 = adaptation recovers nearly all
        of it; near 0 = adaptation recovers almost none of it;
        shopping_only_RMSE remains the floor neither naive nor
        adapted can beat without in-domain Shopping training data.

